Ford Protect Extended Service Plan & Maintenance Plan Benefits






What is Lincoln Protect Extended Service Plan? 
Lincoln Protect Extended Service Plan provides Peace of Mind protection and offers many plan and deductible options to protect you from unexpected vehicle repair costs after your New Vehicle Limited Warranty has expired. It covers the parts and labor to repair thousands of key parts for up to 8 years or 125,000 miles. Failure of covered components due to defects in materials and workmanship and normal wear and tear are included. All covered repairs are performed by factory trained technicians and Lincoln Protect Extended Service Plan coverage includes rental vehicle benefits for up to 10 days at $30/day and 24/7 Roadside Assistance.

Benefits of Lincoln Protect Extended Service Plan: 



100% Backed by Ford Motor Company




24/7 Roadside assistance – up to $100 towing assistance, travel expense reimbursement (up to $500 and 3 days per occurrence, tire change, out-of-fuel, lockout assistance and more.




Limit Out-of-Pocket Expenses: you pay only the deductible on covered repairs




100% Transferable – and may increase the resale value if you sell your vehicle




Rental Vehicle Benefits – up to 10 days of rental at $30/day for covered repairs



Learn More







Lincoln Protect Premium Maintenance Plans
Lincoln Protect Premium Maintenance Plans (PMP) give you genuine Peace of Mind from Lincoln Motor Company by covering ALL of your factory required maintenance requirements.  In addition, Lincoln Protect PMP covers the following common “wear and tear” items:  wiper blades, brake pads and linings, shocks/struts, clutch disc, engine belts and hoses.

Included in the Coverage

Oil and Filter changes, multi-point inspections, and tire rotations.
All factory required maintenance per your Owner's Scheduled Maintenance Guide
Covers failure of select wear items including wiper blades, brake pads and linings, and shock absorbers/struts.
Plans available in 5000, 7500, and 10,000 mile intervals for up to 8 years and 150,000 miles.

Learn More






